Package sjc.util

Provides for utility classes.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Diff.ScriptBuilder  
    Function<I,O>
    This interface represents a function that when given an input of type I, its apply method returns an object of type O.
    VoidFunction<I>
    This interface represents a function that process an input of type I.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Diff
    A class to compare vectors of objects.
    Diff.change
    The result of comparison is an "edit script": a chain of change objects.
    DiffPrint
    A simple framework for printing change lists produced by Diff.
    DiffPrint.Base
    A Base class for printing edit scripts produced by Diff.
    DiffPrint.ContextPrint
    Prints an edit script in context diff format.
    DiffPrint.EdPrint
    Prints an edit script in a format suitable for input to ed.
    DiffPrint.NormalPrint
    Print a change list in the standard diff format.
    DiffPrint.UnifiedPrint
    Prints an edit script in context diff format.
    Pair<E1,E2>
    Type-parametric 2-tuple class.
    Triple<E1,E2,E3>
    Type-parametric 3-tuple class.
    Util
    This class contains some utility methods for the StaticJava compiler.

Package sjc.util Description

Provides for utility classes.
